content.description: Climb a small crack from the belay platform, to flaring chimney, to a jam crack, and follow the pro to the top. The gear is there near the top though it is not easy to spot from below.
content.protection:
A standard rack and 2 top anchors

now with Mussy hooks

.

climbs.name: What's Up, Doc?
climbs.fa: Alex A., Srin S., Siva S.

content.description: Start in a dihedral, and follow a thin crack that traverses across slab right. The crux is the next section - to thin slab, to a dihedral.
content.protection: 11 lead bolts and a 2 bolt top anchor.

content.description:
Top rope from

Scooby-Doo

or

Yosemite Sam

anchors, and climb an arête, a small dihedral, and an overhang. After that, join one of the other routes.
content.protection:
Use a toprope anchor.

Now this has Mussy hooks.

climbs.name: Scooby-Doo
climbs.fa: Alex A., Srin S., Siva S.

content.description: Start in a dihedral or do an easier start a few feet to the right, and climb this shallow dihedral to a few underclings.
content.protection:
7 lead bolts and 2 top anchor bolts

now with Mussy hooks

.

climbs.name: Pinky and the Brain
climbs.fa: Alex A., Srin S., Siva S.

content.description:
A 60m rope will work to to the ledge, but be careful. Put a knot in the end of the rope. If you TR it, you need a directional at the overhang and near the top.

Start on easy 4th/5th Class terrain to a ledge just below

Scooby-Doo

, move left, then wander up the face. The bulge is the crux.
content.protection: 14 lead bolts and 2 top anchor bolts.

content.description:
Below the climb there is a belay bolt, as there is a drop off below,

Start get up

to the ledge, climb just right of the arête in a dihedral move, then up and right on easier to Terrain about 5 feet to pass a flake, then back left, (There is a direct start that is harder that goes straight up, for my it’s 5.11) move left  past a blunt arête, near the top is very COOL lieback, going up the upper dihedral.
content.location: Look for a signed trail Cartoon 1-2, to the upper ledge.

content.description:
This is a TR. It can be climbed from

Yosemite Sam's

anchors. The climb has 2 variations. Climb

Yosemite Sam

, for about 5 feet till you can move to the face to the right to some underclings, work way up the face, Or you can do the direct start, 5.11a, and climb a bulge 4 to 5 feet to the right of the crack.
content.location:
It is to the right of

Yosemite Sam

.

climbs.name: Jane Jetson
climbs.fa: Siva S., Srin S., Alex A.

content.description:
Jane Jetson is a toprope variation. Climb a thin seam for about 50 feet, and join

Johnny Quest

.
content.protection:
Use the anchor on

Johnny Quest

.
content.location: Look for a signed trail Cartoon 1-2, to the upper ledge.

content.description:
At the moment, is a toprope. It will be bolted soon, has top anchors, and can be set up as a toprope from

Animaniacs'

anchor. Climb a thin face, the crux, to an arete/dihedral. For a harder finish variation, climb the arete avoids using the slab on the right.
content.protection:
TR off the top anchors of

Amimaniacs

.
content.location:
It is on the left side of the Cartoon wall, left of

Animaniacs

.

content.description: Start on the upper ledge. Climb a face starting just right of the 1st, then move up and left following the holds.
content.location: Look for a signed trail Cartoon 1-2, to the upper ledge.
